description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Operator – Pharmacy Technical Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Great Ormond Street Hospital for Children NHS Foundation Trust (GOSH) is a national centre of excellence in the provision of specialist children&#39;s health care, currently delivering the widest range of specialist care of any children&#39;s hospital in the UK.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic, pro-active and motivated Band 4 Senior Operator to join our friendly Technical Services Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post involves manufacturing a variety of different types of IV medications aseptically prepared for patients in a controlled manufacturing environment. This is a rotational post covering CIVAS, Parental Nutrition &amp; Cytotoxic units. A high level of accuracy is requires as the post involves measuring ingredients for patient dose manufacture. You will need to be able to work efficiently and follow procedures at all times; working on your own or under supervision. Due to the critical nature of our work, you will have to meet the highest standards of discipline, personal hygiene and attention to detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder is expected to be committed to work a&lt;strong&gt; 1 in 6 weekend rota from 9am – 5pm, with a week day off before &amp; after.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate must also have valuable pharmacy aseptic compounding experience. Ability to lead a small team is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;F&lt;strong&gt;or further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Name Tim White Job title Head of Pharmacy Manufacturing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email address timothy.white@gosh.nhs.uk Telephone number 0207 405 9200 Ext 0579&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional contact information - Kelli Lambie Kelly.Lambie@gosh.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
